Agency Manager Vs. Broker Account? Does agency manager have to be licensed?


Agency/Agency Manager Accounts are for:


Producers who work on their own outside a large agency;


Supervisors/managers of small agencies with two or more producers;


Supervisors/managers of an Insurance Organization; or


Supervisors/managers of producer call centers.


Broker Accounts are for producers who work within (a):


An Agency with multiple producers;


Producer call centers;


Insurance Organizations; or


Agency, but are not a manager or supervisor.
